<theorem xmlns="Theorem"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         type="Lemma"
         id="Lem_InvertibilitySimplify"
         xsi:schemaLocation="Theorem file:/C:/xampp/htdocs/moodle/mod/msm/NewSchemas/Theorem.xsd">
   <statement.theorem>
      <para>
         <para.body>Given <math>
               <latex>(n,n)</latex>
            </math>-matrices <math>
               <latex>\Mtrx{A}</latex>
            </math> and <math>
               <latex>\Mtrx{B}</latex>
            </math>, then</para.body>
      </para>
      <para align="center">
         <para.body>
            <math>
               <latex>\Mtrx{A}\Mtrx{B} = \IdMtrx[n]</latex>
            </math>   if and only if   <math>
               <latex>\Mtrx{B}\Mtrx{A} = \IdMtrx[n]</latex>
            </math>.</para.body>
      </para>
   </statement.theorem>
   <proof>
      <proof.block>
         <caption/>
         <proof.block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>We need to show that <math>
                     <latex>\Mtrx{B}\Mtrx{A}=\IdMtrx[n]</latex>
                  </math>. – We first show that <math>
                     <latex>\Mtrx{A}</latex>
                  </math> is invertible: Using row operations and the corresponding row transformation matrices, we obtain</para.body>
            </para>
         </proof.block.body>
      </proof.block>
      <proof.block>
         <caption/>
         <proof.block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>This follows with the previous argument by interchanging the roles of <math>
                     <latex>\Mtrx{A}</latex>
                  </math> and <math>
                     <latex>\Mtrx{B}</latex>
                  </math>.</para.body>
            </para>
         </proof.block.body>
      </proof.block>
   </proof>
</theorem>
